OL,3,CMan jailed for blinding father-of-two
OL,4,Cin 'sickening' glass attack
OL,6,FA man who blinded a father-of-two in a
OL,7,F"sickening and unprovoked" attack in a
OL,8,Fbar has been jailed for more than 10
OL,9,Fyears.
OL,11,FMatthew Syron, 32, fears he may never
OL,12,Fsee his children again after a beer
OL,13,Fglass was smashed into his face on a
OL,14,FBoxing Day night out with friends in
OL,15,FLeeds last year.
