OL,3,CMan jailed for blinding father-of-two
OL,4,Cin 'sickening' glass attack
OL,6,FIn a statement read out in court, his
OL,7,Fmother Sharon said: "Not only has he
OL,8,Ftaken his eyes, he has taken his life
OL,9,F- the life he had before he came a
OL,10,Fvictim of an attack."
OL,12,F'No sign of trouble'
OL,14,FMichael Smith, prosecuting, said on
OL,15,FBoxing Day both men - who were unknown
OL,16,Fto each other - had been watching
OL,17,Frugby and then went to the Revolucion
OL,18,Fde Cuba bar with separate groups of
OL,19,Ffriends.
