OL,4,Cin 'sickening' glass attack
OL,6,FDean challenged one of Mr Syron's
OL,7,Ffriends to an arm wrestle, but Mr
OL,8,FSmith said "there was no sign of
OL,9,Ftrouble".
OL,11,FHe said: "Some time after midnight Mr
OL,12,FSyron was stood at the bar, standing
OL,13,Fnext to some friends.
OL,15,F"The victim felt something push past
OL,16,Fhis shoulder and it appears the
OL,17,Fdefendant leant past him and pushed
OL,18,Fthe glass into his face, with it
OL,19,Fshattering. Mr Syron immediately fell
OL,20,Fto the floor, realising he had gone
OL,21,Fblind.
